{
  "stem": "812.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From what I know, life for us in Germany was very much as it is here for people today.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I lived with my parents, my two-year-older brother, and my-- with my grandparents in Hoya, which is a little town near Hanover.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My grandparents were in a shoe business, and we lived very comfortably.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we-- life was very easy for us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We had-- the shoe business was very successful.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It was in the early-- mid-30s, actually, when things became increasingly less comfortable for us Jews.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "In fact, for my brother, he was born in 1932, I recall being told that even in his carriage stones were thrown by children and passerbys.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] My grandparents were in their late 70s and were ailing.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And even though things were becoming increasingly more difficult in Germany and my parents had felt that it was time to prepare to emigrate, to leave Germany, my grandparents just didn't feel the urgency of the matter and didn't want to leave.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we, of course, could not leave them.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Then in 1938, within 11 days of each other, my grandparents passed away.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "We then immediately made arrangements to emigrate.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Then in 1938, Kristallnacht, November of '38.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "That was the beginnings of the pogrom against the Jews of Germany.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And were-- it was major destructions of synagogues, businesses, Jewish establishments in general.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And it was at that time that my father was taken from us and sent to a concentration camp, Buchenwald.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And it was only because our papers, immigration papers, were ready that my father was released after only 10 days incarceration.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
